reason.tex:
%text
To get $\perp$ distance from origin we need to rewrite the equation of the plane by dividing throughout by $\sqrt{a^2+b^2+c^2}$, where $a$, $b$ and $c$ are the direction ratios of the normal to the plane. 
%

\begin{align}
  2x+3y+z&=14 \\
 \therefore\sqrt{a^2+b^2+c^2}&=\sqrt{2^2+3^2+1^2} \\
    &=\sqrt{4+9+1}=\sqrt{14}
\end{align} \\
%text
Rewrite the equation of the plane as,
%
\begin{align}
  \dfrac{2}{\sqrt{14}}x+\dfrac{3}{\sqrt{14}}y+\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{14}}z&=\dfrac{14}{\sqrt{14}} \\  
  \perp \text{distance from origin} &= \dfrac{14}{\sqrt{14}}=\sqrt{14}

\end{align}

%
